==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|abecedary}}, from {{der|en|ML.|abecedarium||alphabet, ABC primer}}, from {{der|en|LL.|abecedarius||of the alphabet}}, formed from the first four letters of the Latin alphabet + {{m|la|-arius|}}.<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=3}}</ref>

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ˌeɪ.biː.ˈsiː.də.ɹi/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/ˌeɪ.bi.ˈsi.dɚ.i/|/ˌeɪ.bi.ˈsi.də.ɹi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|new=1}}

# {{lb|en|rare}} The [[alphabet]], written out in a teaching book, or carved on a wall; a primer; [[abecedarium]]. {{defdate|from 1350 to 1470}}<ref name=SOED/>
# One that teaches or learns the alphabet or the fundamentals of any subject; [[abecedarian]]. {{defdate|from late 16<sup>th</sup> century}}<ref name=SOED/>

